<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-14T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-14T01:00:00-05:00" n="1006" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1006">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9327/3–1449: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Clark</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-14T14:00:00+08:00">March 14,
                                1949—2 p. m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received March 14—5:10 a. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Cantel 136. FonOff confirms arrival Tihwa Soviet air experts to negotiate
                        extension Sino-Soviet air agreement. Director American Department says
                        Minister Communications will conduct the negotiations with Commissioner
                        Foreign Affairs, Tihwa, Liu, present. Chen indicated Chinese seek greater
                        participation operation, but was not informed re monopolistic provisions.
                        Shall inquire Minister Communications this regard.</p>
                    <p>Sent Department; repeated Nanking 115, Shanghai 82.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>